<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
67. 
<taxonomicName LSID="47EAF88A-544C-58FD-95D1-19FE2E7E55B3" authority="Petrie, Trans &amp; Proc. New Zealand Inst. 45: 271. 1913 [1912]. (Petrie 1913: 271)." authorityName="Petrie, Trans &amp; Proc. New Zealand Inst. 45: 271. 1913 [1912]. (Petrie" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus fractosaxosus" order="Solanales" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fractosaxosus">Convolvulus fractosaxosus Petrie, Trans &amp; Proc. New Zealand Inst. 45: 271. 1913 [1912]. (Petrie 1913: 271).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
NEW ZEALAND, South Island, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Cockayne</emphasis>
s.n. (holotype WELT-4828).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
Greyish-pubescent creeping herb arising from underground rhizome; stems to 30 cm. Leaves petiolate, 1.5-3.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.8 cm, dimorphic and very variable, mostly deltoid or ovate, sometimes hastate and always with some leaves with an oblong or linear terminal lobe 1-5 cm long, combined with small basal auricles arising at right angles to the terminal lobe; petioles 1-5 cm. Flowers solitary, axillary, pedunculate; peduncles 2-6 cm long, 1-flowered, slender, pubescent; bracteoles 2-3 mm long, linear; pedicels 2-6 mm, pubescent; outer sepals 6-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-6 mm, broadly ovate, pubescent, larger than inner sepals; corolla 1.7-2 cm long, white, midpetaline bands pink; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided 6-7 mm above base. Capsule glabrous; seeds finely tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, LB" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Wellington" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 234" refId="B236" refString="Moore, LB, Irwin, JB, 1978. The Oxford book of New Zealand plants. Oxford University Press, Wellington: 1 - 234" title="The Oxford book of New Zealand plants" year="1978">Moore and Irwin 1978</bibRefCitation>
: 157]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
New Zealand: South Island (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Travers</emphasis>
1864, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Hombron</emphasis>
1841), 300-1600 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
Similar to forms of the Australian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Br., Prodr. Fl. Nov. Holland 482. 1810. (Brown" authorityYear="1810" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus angustissimus" order="Solanales" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustissimus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Convolvulus angustissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Tasmania and Victoria but corolla and sepals slightly longer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
